        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Alright, at 57 here's what I'm doing. </P><P>Spells used: Servant of Bones (rogue pet wouldn't be too shabby eihter), Augmentation of Death, Invoke Fear, Dooming Darkness, Vexing Mordania (could be swapped for BoD I suppose for you sub-57s), Lich (damn demi for being so rare...), Deflux, Paralyzing Earth, Shield of the Magi. Some of those don't need to be memmed, so throw whatever you want into any spare slots you have.</P><P>1) Set up inside the graveyard. If you're facing the building with the gargoyles, it's the corner on your right. Summon and buff pet, throw up shielding if you're so inclined.</P><P>2)Go into lich, recover some of the pet mana and have a decently low hp total. Then go pull a guard outside the graveyard with Vexing. Run along the path in the graveyard until you hit the building, then turn right and run to your pet.</P><P>3) Dark, pet, fear, refear, loot.</P><P>Some notes: Graveyard has some screwy pathing. If you try something other than what I explained, guards may warp. Also, guards may warp to the graveyard entrance at any time for no reason at all. Just 'flux them down or drag your pet over. Also, sometimes the guards "shift". Basically, whatever guard you're killing poofs. That's life. Try and time it or just suck a little inefficiency. Root is for those corpses that reanimate and beat on you while you're running through the graveyard if you're not careful. If you ARE careful, just run once you see the message and you won't be aggroed.</P><P>With all this lazy man's soloing, I got a yellow in 4 hours, and that's counting breaks for food, piss poor internet connections (DON'T GET QWEST!!!) and people pestering me. Not bad at all.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

