        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I should have read the post from Oznusyen about killing the bank guards area till non-kos.  The undead were a pain.  Ya, I could avoide them when they popped, but that was usually when I was headed out to get a guard.  So what do I do, wait till de-pop or get aggro on the way back in?</P><P>Go to the bank is what you do.  Those undead have a huge aggro range.  </P><P>Bank tacktics, darkness, root, splurt, BoD, pet, Pact, Fear.  Dead guard.  I did the two by the bank you can see coming down the stairs, then the two at the stairs, then the one above.  I was pulling to the wall below were the ramp starts to go up.  Had to leave after those five, but there were two more by a door next to where I was that were going to be next.  Fear pathing went up the stairs and I had a hard time with "can't see mob to cast on them" messages, but your milage might vary.  You could also fear kite once you get rid of the two by the stairs.  When I pulled the guard on the far side of the stairs from me he pathed way over by the bank.  I was glad I had killed the two guards there first.</P><P>I wonder if I can use the bank if I kill all the gaurds around it?</P><P>-DV</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
